      B: 'A self-fulfilling prophecy involves acting in ways that confirm an expectation, often by changing effort or behavior. Stereotype threat is more precisely about the cognitive and emotional burden of the threatened identity during performance, not a belief about failure leading to reduced effort. Also, the self-fulfilling prophecy concept applies more broadly and is not the best specific label for this paradigm.',
