      D: 'Learned helplessness (Seligman) results from repeated exposure to uncontrollable negative outcomes, leading to a generalized belief that effort cannot change outcomes. Stereotype threat is situationally activated by framing cues in the test context, not built up through repeated experiences of helplessness.',
